<DOCNO> APW20000613.0006 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-13 00:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NY Cheers Springsteen's Diallo Song  </HEADLINE>
By DONNA DE LA CRUZ
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- To loud cheers and scattered boos, Bruce
Springsteen sang about the New York City killing of Amadou Diallo
during the musician's opening night of a 10-show stand at Madison
Square Garden.
</P>
<P>
   Bandmembers approached microphones one by one Monday and
repeated the words ''41 shots,'' referring to the number of times
four white officers shot at Diallo, a black West African immigrant.
</P>
<P>
   One heckler was escorted from the Garden after he approached the
stage and flashed obscene hand gestures at Springsteen during the
song.
</P>
<P>
   A police union had urged its members to stay away from the
concert in protest of the new song, ''American Skin (41 Shots).''
</P>
<P>
   Diallo, 22, was fatally wounded as he stood in the vestibule of
his Bronx home on Feb. 4, 1999. He was struck by 19 bullets. The
four officers were acquitted of murder earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
   The song, the seventh of the show, did not mention Diallo's
name, and Springsteen said nothing about it before or after he
sang.
</P>
<P>
   ''Is this your wallet? Is this your life?'' he sang, referring
to Diallo's wallet, which police mistook for a gun.
</P>
<P>
   At another point, he sang ''You can get killed just for living
in your American skin.''
</P>
<P>
   A family friend said Diallo's parents planned to attend the
concert to thank Springsteen for the song. Their presence could not
be immediately confirmed.
</P>
<P>
   Spokespeople for Springsteen did not return repeated telephone
messages for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Springsteen introduced ''American Skin'' last week during a
concert in Atlanta with his E Street Band. The song is unrecorded
and unreleased.
</P>
<P>
   The Patrolmen's Benevolent Association, which represents the
city's 27,000 police officers, has urged its members not to attend
or work overtime security detail at Springsteen's Garden concerts.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   Springsteen fan site: http://www.luckytown.org
</P>
<P>
   PBA: http://www.nycpba.org
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-13-00 0041 </TRAILER>
