Mariners 5, Royals 3
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Edgar Martinez homered and drove in four runs to
power Seattle past the Kansas City Royals 5-3 Monday night and give the Mariners
their best record after 60 games. Seattle, which has won six of eight, raised
its record to 33-27 and move into first place in the AL West, a half-game ahead
of Oakland. The Mariners' previous best was 32-28, accomplished three times,
most recently in 1997.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
