<HEADLINE> Anti-Kidnapping Investigator Dead  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CUERNAVACA, Mexico (AP) -- An anti-kidnapping investigator has
been found dead along a highway in central Mexico, authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
   Poseidon Rios Ramirez, 34, was run over by a car along the
central Mexican highway between Cuernavaca and Acapulco. His body
was found Monday. Morelos state Attorney General Rogelio Sanchez
Gatica said authorities have not ruled out foul play.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez, an investigator in the Morelos district attorney's
office, worked with a special state anti-kidnapping unit.
Kidnappings for ransom have become one of Mexico's most feared
crimes in recent years, with victims ranging from middle-class
farmers to the president of Mexico's largest bank.
</P>
<P>
   A number of the kidnappings have occurred in Morelos. The
state's governor and top police officials were toppled in 1998
after the state police anti-kidnapping unit itself was implicated
in kidnappings.
</P>
