<HEADLINE> Dow, Nasdaq Slip Slightly  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down two
points in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York
Stock Exchange hold a 6-5 lead over losers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 21 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up two points.
</P>
<P>
   It looks like some mixed currents for the markets today.
</P>
<P>
   On the plus side, a government report showed a decline in retail
sales for May. Investors have been looking for signs the economy is
growing at a more sustainable pace.
</P>
<P>
   On the minus side, a Wall Street brokerage has downgraded shares
of Hewlett-Packard, which is a component of the Dow.
</P>
<P>
   And on the uncertain side, Fed chairman Alan Greenspan delivers
a speech to economists in New York later today.
</P>
