<HEADLINE> Stocks Slip in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly lower at the start of trading
Tuesday. Technology investors were girding for another rough
session after Wall Street investment firm Sanford Bernstein cut its
rating and earnings estimates for Hewlett-Packard.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after the start of trading, the Dow Jones industrial
average was down 53.39 at 10,510.82.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index was down 24.07 at 3,743.84, but the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 1.01 at 1,447.01.
</P>
<P>
   Hewlett-Packard, a Dow component, was down $6.563 at $119.438,
accounting for most of the Dow's loss.
