<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Cuban Business Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HAVANA (AP) -- The Associated Press reported erroneously on June
9 and June 10 that a United Airlines representative was among
American business people at a US-Cuba Business Summit in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   The Italian firm that sponsored the event, Cristobal srl, gave
reporters a list of participants that included an international
representative of United Airlines.
</P>
<P>
   But Raffaello Pellegrini, a representative of Cristobal srl,
said later the list hadn't been updated to reflect those actually
there. He said no United Airlines representative had traveled to
Havana for the summit.
</P>
