<HEADLINE> Jerry Hall To Play Mrs. Robinson  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Jerry Hall is getting ready to bare all on stage.
</P>
<P>
   The model and ex-wife of Mick Jagger has been tapped to replace
Kathleen Turner in the West End production of ''The Graduate,'' the
Gielgud Theater announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Turner steps aside on July 29. After that, Hall will take over
the role of the seductress Mrs. Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   The play, which has set box-office records despite lukewarm
reviews, is expected to be extended until the end of the year.
Adapted from the 1967 film starring Dustin Hoffman and Anne
Bancroft, it has attracted bountiful publicity for a brief scene in
which Turner appears naked onstage.
</P>
<P>
   Hall, 43, is expected to also appear nude.
</P>
<P>
   Hall and Jagger divorced last year. The couple have four
children.
</P>
