<HEADLINE> Tuckahoe policeman admits sex with boy  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) - A policeman who had been considered a
community asset admitted in court Tuesday that he engaged in sex
with a 16-year-old boy in the back seat of his car.
</P>
<P>
   In exchange for his guilty plea to third-degree sodomy, former
Tuckahoe police Officer Stanley Moore will get a sentence without
jail time. Prosecutors said they agreed to the deal only because
the stress of the case was threatening the victim's life.
</P>
<P>
   District Attorney Jeanine Pirro said the boy had attempted
suicide several times and doctors felt ''the very pendency of this
case has posed a life-threatening stress level to the victim.''
</P>
<P>
   Moore, 47, was a 16-year veteran of the Tuckahoe force and was
active in various civic endeavors. He had ''a reputation for being
a good cop, a good detective,'' Pirro said.
</P>
<P>
   But on March 12, he was arrested when a Westchester County
police officer on routine patrol saw him naked with the boy in the
car, parked at a county maintenance lot.
</P>
<P>
   Moore's sentence will include five years probation and
registration as a sex offender, Pirro said.
</P>
<P>
   Tuckahoe police Chief Gerard Mignone said Moore, who had been
suspended after his arrest, resigned Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was afforded his due process, which concludes one chapter
in his life and continues on to what lies ahead,'' the chief said.
</P>
</TEXT>
