<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mystics 57, Liberty 56  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Chamique Holdsclaw scored 23 points and hit the
game-winning jumper with 10.8 seconds left as the Washington
Mystics defeated the New York Liberty 57-56 Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Holdsclaw drove past Sue Wicks and Teresa Weatherspoon before
hitting a 10-foot jumper.
</P>
<P>
   Becky Hammon missed a baseline jumper with 3.5 seconds left, and
Tari Phillips missed another attempt at the buzzer.
</P>
<P>
   Nikki McCray added nine points for the Mystics (4-2), who beat
the Liberty (3-5) for the fifth time in six meetings.
</P>
<P>
   Vickie Johnson and Weatherspoon scored 14 points each and Hammon
had 13 for New York. Johnson's driving layup gave New York a 56-55
lead with 39 seconds left before Holdsclaw hit the game-winner.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 55-51 with 1:28 remaining, the Liberty stole the
inbound pass and Hammon hit a 3-pointer. Weatherspoon then
deflected a pass intended for Vicky Bullett off her fingers and the
Liberty got possession with 50 seconds remaining to set up
Johnson's layup.
</P>
<P>
   Phillips, playing with a hairline fracture of her right big toe,
had 10 points and 12 rebounds for New York.
</P>
<P>
   Holdsclaw, recovering from two stress fractures in her right
foot, finished 10-for-21 from the field and grabbed 12 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Leading by three at halftime, New York opened its biggest lead,
37-28, after Wicks blocked Holdsclaw's shot and Johnson converted a
fastbreak layup. Holdsclaw then scored six straight points and Nagy
made a 3-pointer to it.
</P>
<P>
   After a steal by Bullett, Nagy fed an alley-oop pass to
Holdsclaw that she banked off the glass for a 45-43 lead with 9:40
remaining.
</P>
<P>
   New York's Crystal Robinson, in her second game back after
missing four with a sprained left ankle, shot 0-for-7 from the
field. Robinson scored 19 points on 8-for-12 shooting in Saturday's
victory against Indiana.
</P>
<P>
   Holdsclaw scored six of her 10 first-half points on consecutive
baskets to give the Mystics an early 18-16 lead. Hammon scored 10
points in the final seven minutes of the opening period, including
a 3-pointer for a 23-20 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Tausha Mills, the No. 2 pick for the Mystics in the draft, made
two straight layups before Johnson's 18-foot jumper gave the
Liberty a 29-26 lead at halftime.
</P>
</TEXT>
