<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Pinch-runner Damon Buford scored from second on a
throwing error by shortstop Kurt Abbott in the eighth inning,
lifting the Chicago Cubs to a 4-3 victory over the New York Mets on
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   With the game tied 3-3 and one out in the eighth, Henry
Rodriguez singled off John Franco (2-2) and was removed for Buford.
Joe Girardi singled, advancing Buford to second, and pinch-hitter
Glenallen Hill hit a grounder to first baseman Todd Zeile. He threw
