<HEADLINE> Denker Named Santa Clara Coach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTA CLARA Calif. (AP) -- Santa Clara dropped the interim from
Chris Denker's title Tuesday and made him the women's head
basketball coach.
</P>
<P>
   Denker was an assistant coach at Santa Clara for the past seven
years, serving as the top recruiting and offensive coordinator.
</P>
<P>
   In those seven years, the team had a 137-64 record, including
69-29 in the West Coast Conference, and won three WCC
championships.
</P>
<P>
   The coaching staff will not change much with Denker's
advancement. Second-year assistant coach Anita Kaplan will stay on
as will first-year assistants Jeff Dow and Benita Martin.
</P>
<P>
   Santa Clara will have three starters returning from last
season's team that went 21-9.
</P>
<P>
   Denker was appointed interim coach in April when Caren
Horstmeyer left Santa Clara after 12 years to become head coach at
California.
</P>
